#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "thag12.1:4.1"
msgid "12.1. Sīlavattheragāthā"
msgstr ""

#. </h1></div><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a
#. class="verse-num-sc" id="verse-num-sc608"></a><a class="verse-num-pts"
#. id="verse-num-pts608"></a><a class="pts" id="pts63"></a>
msgctxt "thag12.1:5.1"
msgid "“Sīlamevidha sikkhetha,"
msgstr "One should train just in virtue,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:5.2"
msgid "asmiṃ loke susikkhitaṃ;"
msgstr "For in this world, when virtue is"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:5.3"
msgid "Sīlañhi sabbasampattiṃ,"
msgstr "Cultivated and well-trained,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:5.4"
msgid "upanāmeti sevitaṃ."
msgstr "It provides all success."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc609"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts609"></a>
msgctxt "thag12.1:6.1"
msgid "Sīlaṃ rakkheyya medhāvī,"
msgstr "Desiring three kinds of happiness—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:6.2"
msgid "patthayāno tayo sukhe;"
msgstr "Praise, prosperity,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:6.3"
msgid "Pasaṃsaṃ vittilābhañca,"
msgstr "And to delight in heaven after passing away—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:6.4"
msgid "<span class=\"var\" title=\"pecca sagge ca modanaṃ (bj, pts1-2)\" id=\"note288\">pecca sagge pamodanaṃ</span>."
msgstr "The wise should protect virtue."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc610"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts610"></a>
msgctxt "thag12.1:7.1"
msgid "Sīlavā hi bahū mitte,"
msgstr "The well-behaved have many friends,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:7.2"
msgid "saññamenādhigacchati;"
msgstr "Because of their self-restraint."

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:7.3"
msgid "Dussīlo pana mittehi,"
msgstr "But one without virtue, of bad conduct,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:7.4"
msgid "dhaṃsate pāpamācaraṃ."
msgstr "Drives away their friends."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc611"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts611"></a>
msgctxt "thag12.1:8.1"
msgid "Avaṇṇañca akittiñca,"
msgstr "A person of bad behavior has"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:8.2"
msgid "dussīlo labhate naro;"
msgstr "Ill-repute and infamy."

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:8.3"
msgid "Vaṇṇaṃ kittiṃ pasaṃsañca,"
msgstr "A person of virtue always has"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:8.4"
msgid "sadā labhati sīlavā."
msgstr "A good reputation, fame, and praise."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc612"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts612"></a>
msgctxt "thag12.1:9.1"
msgid "Ādi sīlaṃ patiṭṭhā ca,"
msgstr "Virtue is the starting point and foundation;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:9.2"
msgid "kalyāṇānañca mātukaṃ;"
msgstr "The mother at the head"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:9.3"
msgid "Pamukhaṃ sabbadhammānaṃ,"
msgstr "Of all good qualities:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:9.4"
msgid "tasmā sīlaṃ visodhaye."
msgstr "Therefore you should purify virtue."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc613"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts613"></a>
msgctxt "thag12.1:10.1"
msgid "Velā ca <span class=\"var\" title=\"saṃvaro sīlaṃ (bj) | saṃvarasīlaṃ (bj-a)\" id=\"note289\">saṃvaraṃ sīlaṃ</span>,"
msgstr "Virtue is a boundary and a restraint,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:10.2"
msgid "cittassa abhihāsanaṃ;"
msgstr "An enjoyment for the mind;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:10.3"
msgid "Titthañca sabbabuddhānaṃ,"
msgstr "The place where all the Buddhas cross over:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:10.4"
msgid "tasmā sīlaṃ visodhaye."
msgstr "Therefore you should purify virtue."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc614"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts614"></a>
msgctxt "thag12.1:11.1"
msgid "Sīlaṃ balaṃ appaṭimaṃ,"
msgstr "Virtue is the matchless power;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:11.2"
msgid "sīlaṃ āvudhamuttamaṃ;"
msgstr "Virtue is the ultimate weapon;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:11.3"
msgid "Sīlamābharaṇaṃ seṭṭhaṃ,"
msgstr "Virtue is the best ornament;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:11.4"
msgid "sīlaṃ kavacamabbhutaṃ."
msgstr "Virtue is a marvellous coat of armour."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc615"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts615"></a>
msgctxt "thag12.1:12.1"
msgid "Sīlaṃ setu mahesakkho,"
msgstr "Virtue is a mighty bridge;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:12.2"
msgid "sīlaṃ gandho anuttaro;"
msgstr "Virtue is the unsurpassed scent;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:12.3"
msgid "Sīlaṃ vilepanaṃ seṭṭhaṃ,"
msgstr "Virtue is the best perfume,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:12.4"
msgid "yena vāti disodisaṃ."
msgstr "That floats in all directions."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc616"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts616"></a>
msgctxt "thag12.1:13.1"
msgid "Sīlaṃ sambalamevaggaṃ,"
msgstr "Virtue is the best provision;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:13.2"
msgid "sīlaṃ pātheyyamuttamaṃ;"
msgstr "Virtue is the unsurpassed supply for a journey;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:13.3"
msgid "Sīlaṃ seṭṭho ativāho,"
msgstr "Virtue is the best vehicle,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:13.4"
msgid "yena yāti disodisaṃ."
msgstr "That takes you in all directions."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc617"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts617"></a>
msgctxt "thag12.1:14.1"
msgid "Idheva nindaṃ labhati,"
msgstr "In this life they’re criticized;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:14.2"
msgid "peccāpāye ca dummano;"
msgstr "After passing away they’re unhappy in a lower realm;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:14.3"
msgid "Sabbattha dummano bālo,"
msgstr "A fool is unhappy everywhere,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:14.4"
msgid "sīlesu asamāhito."
msgstr "Because they are not endowed with virtues."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc618"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts618"></a>
msgctxt "thag12.1:15.1"
msgid "Idheva kittiṃ labhati,"
msgstr "In this life they’re famous;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:15.2"
msgid "pecca sagge ca summano;"
msgstr "After passing away they’re happy in heaven;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:15.3"
msgid "Sabbattha sumano dhīro,"
msgstr "A person with understanding is happy everywhere,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:15.4"
msgid "sīlesu susamāhito."
msgstr "Because they are endowed with virtues."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="verse-num-sc"
#. id="verse-num-sc619"></a><a class="verse-num-pts" id="verse-num-pts619"></a>
msgctxt "thag12.1:16.1"
msgid "Sīlameva idha aggaṃ,"
msgstr "Virtue is best in this life,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:16.2"
msgid "paññavā pana uttamo;"
msgstr "But person with understanding is supreme"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:16.3"
msgid "Manussesu ca devesu,"
msgstr "Among humans and gods,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "thag12.1:16.4"
msgid "sīlapaññāṇato jayan”ti."
msgstr "Conquering with virtue and understanding."

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "thag12.1:17.1"
msgid "…"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "thag12.1:17.2"
msgid "Sīlavo thero …."
msgstr ""

